						               													<description>Billionaires from all sorts of dimensions have traveled through wormholes in space and time and have arrived in the same place. They all have one goal in mind... to become the first trillionaire in the universe (or universes)!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Trillionaire is a card game that comes with pre-built, balanced decks so it can be played right out of the box. Players continue battling until one obtains 10 Cash Cards ($1 Trillion worth) and successfully deposits their full Trillion into the bank. You can only obtain sufficient Cash Cards for victory by Bankrupting opponents' Billionaire Cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Billionaires range from a sentient computer from Neato Prime, who philanthropically solves global problems, to a space traveling asteroid miner from the Bermuda Wormhole dimension. Each player must &amp;lsquo;Lawyer up&amp;rsquo; their Billionaires to make them ready for battle with opposing Billionaires, while also playing Control Cards to influence their own and other players&amp;rsquo; actions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every player starts with a deck of 60 cards. Players may use one of the pre-built decks, or each player's deck may be customized before play begins. Trillionaire was designed from the start to be both highly customizable and strategic.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are four categories of cards which make up each deck:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Cash Cards - Worth $100 Billion each, these cards are the heart of the game. If you successfully put 10 Cash Cards on the table, you may attempt to deposit them to win the game!&amp;#10;     Billionaire Cards - These character cards serve as your front line to Sue and Bankrupt your opponents' Billionaires. Comes in &amp;quot;Standard&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;Super&amp;quot; varieties.&amp;#10;     Lawyer Cards - These cards are attached to your Billionaire Cards, enabling them to Sue your opponents. Without them, your Billionaires wouldn't be able to do anything. Comes in &amp;quot;Standard&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;Power&amp;quot; varieties.&amp;#10;     Control Cards - These cards help you control the game in your favor. Some involve greater risk, but have a greater reward.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If players choose to customize their decks, they must follow certain rules:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     There are no more than 10 Star Cards allowed per deck. (Every card is either a Star Card or a Non-Star Card.)&amp;#10;     Your deck must contain exactly 15 Cash Cards. &amp;#10;     All players must have exactly 1 Veto Card in their deck.&amp;#10;     Players may only have up to 3 of any card that is not a Cash Card, Standard Lawyer, or Veto card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Trillionaire can be played with a teammate (2 v 2) or as a free-for-all (up to 4 players).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
